[4] Sri Lanka
Date: Sat 24 Jul 2010
Source: Viva Lanka [edited]
<http://vivalanka.com/n/p?i=90498>


The Epidemiology Unit of the Health Ministry states that the outbreak
of dengue fever has caused 164 deaths, while 22 159 cases have been
reported so far this year [2010]. The Unit reported that the highest
number of deaths of 45 had been reported from the Colombo district,
followed by Gampaha district with 21 deaths and Jaffna district with
16 deaths.

Out of the 45 from Colombo district, 20 were reported from the Colombo
Municipal Council limits, while the other 25 were reported from areas
including the Dehiwala-Mt. Lavinia Municipal Council, which has been
declared a dengue high risk zone since last week.

The highest number of dengue patients, amounting to 3341, has been
recorded in the month of July 2010 between the 1st and 24th of the
month [2010].

