[7] Trinidad & Tobago
Date: Fri 23 Jul 2010
Source: i95.5FM [edited]
<http://www.i955fm.com/News.aspx?id=8848>


The Chief Medical Officer, Dr. Anton Cumberbatch, is now confirming
that there is a dengue fever outbreak in Trinidad and Tobago. The
announcement was made at a news conference hosted by the Ministry of
Health earlier today [23 Jul 2010]. Dr. Cumberbatch said 3 of 5 deaths
are now confirmed as dengue related, but an outbreak is not only
determined by the number of people who die of the disease. He said the
rate of infection is increasing, and there are now about 600 reported
cases. The C.M.O. said there is no telling how many people have the
disease and have sought treatment privately.

--
